International passengers who arrive without a valid COVID-19 test will be pulled over. AFP/Rodger Bosch JOHANNESBURG - Cape Town International Airport has been crowned the best airport in Africa again. This is the seventh consecutive year that the airport has won this title at the World Airport Awards held in Paris. The airport also bagged the 'Best Staff in Africa’ and ‘Cleanest Airport in Africa’ accolades. Travellers from across the globe take part in the airport customer satisfaction survey to decide the winners. The survey evaluates customer experience across different airport services. Meanwhile, King Shaka International Airport defended its Best Regional Airport in Africa title. InterContinental Hotel at OR Tambo International Airport was voted 'Best Airport Hotel on the continent. Cape Town International Airport has been crowned the best airport in Africa, again! This is the 7th consecutive year that the airport has won this title at the World Airport Awards held in Paris.#DStv403 pic.twitter.com/gOYxzEw4mD